steps.userPrompt:
Review the following watchlist data:

{{load-watchlist.output}}

If the watchlist is empty (no incidents listed), call orchestra_complete with status 'success' and reason 'Watchlist is empty, no incidents to track'. If there ARE incidents in the list, output ONLY a JSON array of the incident IDs as strings, e.g. ["770343639", "760607426"]. No other text.

Fetch full details and description entries for each of these tracked incidents:

{{check-watchlist.output}}

For each incident ID:
1. Get the incident details
2. Get the description entries (comments)

Output a single JSON object with this structure:
{
  "<incident_id>": {
    "incident": { ...incident details... },
    "descriptions": [ ...description entries... ]
  }
}

. **Always** return ONLY the JSON content that you fetched. Important, return the json content only (of the IcM that you fetched!), nothing more, nothing else

Retrieve the previously stored snapshots for each of these incidents:

{{check-watchlist.output}}

For each incident ID, use the get_memory tool with the incident ID as the key. The category is already set to 'icm-tracker'.

Output a JSON object mapping each incident ID to its stored data, or null if no previous snapshot exists:
{
  "<incident_id>": { ...previous data or null... }
}

Output ONLY the JSON, no other text.

Compare the current incident data against the previous snapshots and identify all changes.

Watchlist (for labels):
{{load-watchlist.output}}

Current incident data:
{{fetch-incident-details.output}}

Previous snapshots:
{{load-previous-snapshots.output}}

For incidents with no previous snapshot (null), treat everything as 'new' (first time tracking) - report the current state as a summary rather than listing every field as a change.

Output a JSON object with this structure:
{
  "hasChanges": true/false,
  "incidents": {
    "<incident_id>": {
      "label": "<from watchlist>",
      "isNew": true/false,
      "changes": [
        {
          "field": "<what changed>",
          "from": "<old value or null if new>",
          "to": "<new value>"
        }
      ],
      "newComments": [
        {
          "author": "<who>",
          "date": "<when>",
          "text": "<comment summary>"
        }
      ],
      "currentState": "<current incident state>",
      "currentSeverity": <severity number>
    }
  }
}

If hasChanges is false (no changes for any incident), use the orchestra_set_status tool with status 'no_action' and reason 'No changes detected for any tracked incident'. Still output the JSON.
